    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">431 Stevens Street<ptr target="pml.00048_n1"/></name>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">Camden New Jersey</name>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">U S A</name>&#8212;
                    <date when="1881-01-01">Jan: 1 '81</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>

            <p>Was sorry&#8212;extremely sorry&#8212;to hear of your illness&#8212;trust you are
                well again by this time, (as fore-indicated by H[erbert]'s last)<ptr
                    target="pml.00048_n2"/>&#8212;all H's books for Mrs S[tafford] came safely<ptr
                        target="pml.00048_n3"/>&#8212;also letters &amp; p.o. order&#8212;<choice><orig>rec'd</orig><reg>received</reg></choice> the
                good, long, fine letter from B[eatrice]<ptr target="pml.00048_n4"/>&#8212;The S's
                are all well as usual&#8212;I am getting along capitally for me this winter so
                far&#8212;have been &amp; am writing quite a deal <hi rend="italic">to order</hi>
                (astonishing, isn't it?)<ptr target="pml.00048_n5"/>&#8212;will surely send you when
                in print&#8212;I wish you would send the <hi rend="italic">Cedar-Plums like</hi><ptr
                    target="pml.00048_n6"/> to Rossetti&#8212;(I suppose you rec'd it)&#8212;what
                silly fictitious items appear about me in some of the English papers&#8212;(about as
                bad as <hi rend="italic">here</hi>)&#8212;trust you all had merry Christmas &amp;
                New Year's&#8212;Cold &amp; deep snow here&#8212;</p>

            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">WW</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
